data.content:
## What breaks in .NET 11

In .NET 11, the **sync-over-async opt-in for the EF Core Cosmos DB provider is removed**. The temporary compatibility shim you configured in .NET 10 no longer exists.

Every synchronous LINQ operator (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`) and `SaveChanges()` will throw an **`InvalidOperationException`** at runtime — with no way to suppress it.

### The fix: convert to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key points:**
- `Add()` is fine — it's an in-memory operation, not a DB call
- All callers up the chain must also become `async`/`await` (this ripples up to controllers)
- Remove the old sync-over-async opt-in from your `DbContext` configuration — it will cause a build error since the API no longer exists
